leadership planning and recruitment office of institutional planning stanford university school of medicine stanford school of medicine office of institutional planning search this site only stanford medical sites ways to give find a person alumni lane library ways to give find a person leadership planning and recruitment a good leader inspires people to have confidence in the leader a great leader inspires people to have confidence in themselves anonymous the office of institutional planning assists the school with the recruitment of senior academic leadership a critical component in the future development of the school the office of institutional planning provides professional assistance to the search committee by developing a set of recruitment information materials providing staff to manage the search committee through the systematic execution of a rigorous and standardized search process and finally with the final stages of the recruitment following the delivery of a short list to the dean who then takes responsibility for the conclusion of the recruitment recruitment of senior academic leadership at stanford follows a structured process see recruiting academic leadership that is designed to recruit the best possible candidate through a process that is conducted with integrity and transparency is thorough and comprehensive maximizes resources to insure and maintain a diverse candidate pool moves expeditiously and systematically respects confidentiality provides candidates with access to information leaves all involved with a sense of fairness supports a final decision by the dean for additional information on senior academic leadership planning and recruitment or for guidance on other leadership recruitment please contact kendra baldwin for assistance with faculty recruitment please consult the office of academic affairs guide to faculty searches you are here stanford medicine school of medicine the dean's office office of institutional planning leadership plan